ice in the companys most recently reported quarter revenue was up  and nongaap earnings per share were up  both year over year perhaps more importantly the number of active accounts grew to  million up  from the year before and transactions per account increased to  up  of course all this is looking to the past what paypal investors really need to know is how the company will perform going forward with that in mind here are three possible catalysts for paypals stock in  pay with venmo venmo paypals peertopeer payment app is hugely popular with millennials who use it continually to split pizza among friends and share uber fares in s third quarter venmo processed  billion in payment volume up  year over year and up more than  from the prior quarter image source paypal holdings inc paypal obviously doesnt have a problem driving user growth on venmo the companys dilemma has been to find ways to make a profit through the app without jeopardizing its popularity paypal management believes the solution is pay with venmo a program that allows venmo account holders to make purchases from participating merchants at the beginning of  paypal reported approximately  venmo users were participating in the program by the end of the year it was available for all venmo users paypal management has said they are actively growing the merchant base for the program early data is encouraging ceo dan schulman said in the companys thirdquarter conference call that account holders who use pay with venmo are  more engaged than other venmo users given its popularity any method the company finds to monetize venmo could prove to be a financial boon paypal one touch paypals one touch allows account holders to authenticate their accounts the first time they use the platform to make an online purchase and then skip the log in process in subsequent uses consumers love the product because it saves them the time and hassle of retrieving their usernames and passwords and entering in all other pertinent information for every single purchase retailers love the product because it crushes the competition at online sales conversions according to a comscore study released last april paypals one touch converts an astounding  of all customers who enter a payment method during an online checkout process into an actual sale the closest competitor converted  its no wonder that one touch is the most rapidly adopted product in paypals history one touch is now available in over  markets in paypals thirdquarter conference call schulman stated that  million consumers and more than  million merchants were using the product by the end of  schulman projected that would increase to  million consumers and  million merchants ecommerce is paypals bread and butter with the rapid adoption and use of one touch paypal could well continue to dominate this arena for years to come stronger profits from xoom in november  paypal completed its acquisition of xoom the international remittance company in the thirdquarter earnings report paypal announced the addition of  new countries available for the xoom platform this means xooms domestic customers can now send money to friends or loved ones in over  countries in  of those countries xoom recipients can now send requests for money or bill payments image source paypal holdings inc consumers also can now link their paypal and xoom accounts a move that should drive account growth for both platforms in the  firstquarter conference call ceo schulman acknowledged xoom was currently margin dilutive and would likely remain so for the rest of  in the thirdquarter call he again admitted xoom had been a drag on our margins but he stated he fully expected xoom to start generating more significant profits in  given the additional countries available to the platform the new request feature and the integration of paypal and xoom accounts now available i wouldnt bet against that prediction this year matthew cochrane owns shares of paypal holdings the motley fool o